1
00:00:21,689 --> 00:00:23,357
<i>Mr. Cruz, I'm so sorry.</i>

2
00:00:23,441 --> 00:00:26,360
We did everything we could,
but your wife lost the baby.

3
00:00:26,444 --> 00:00:29,488
Let's meet at the old café in Baltazar.
No funny business.

4
00:00:29,572 --> 00:00:31,741
- <i>Where's Teo?</i>
- <i>We're not going anywhere</i>

5
00:00:31,824 --> 00:00:33,159
<i>until I see Issay!</i>

6
00:00:33,242 --> 00:00:36,746
Before we escape,
we should at least weaken them.

7
00:00:36,829 --> 00:00:39,832
Next, we'll take down
their human trafficking operations.

8
00:00:39,915 --> 00:00:41,834
<i>Divino has my laptop now.</i>

9
00:00:41,917 --> 00:00:44,170
<i>I'll break into the law office</i>
<i>of Divino and Ace.</i>

10
00:00:44,253 --> 00:00:46,756
- <i>It contains all the evidence.</i>
- Don't move!

11
00:00:46,839 --> 00:00:49,467
Attorney San Juan,
who is the head of the whole operation?

12
00:00:49,550 --> 00:00:53,345
Pearl Valdez. Mateo Crisanto's mother.

13
00:00:53,429 --> 00:00:55,556
I am Divino Verona's right hand.

14
00:00:55,639 --> 00:00:56,974
All the transactions are there.

15
00:00:57,057 --> 00:01:00,811
- You know a lot about this.
- <i>I was his mistress.</i>

16
00:01:02,354 --> 00:01:05,691
♪ <i>Love is never gone... ♪</i>

17
00:01:35,846 --> 00:01:38,015
As logistics manager,

18
00:01:38,098 --> 00:01:41,101
I handled all company portals.

19
00:01:41,185 --> 00:01:43,979
From 2020 to 2025,

20
00:01:44,063 --> 00:01:47,233
over 80 billion pesos passed
through our offshore accounts.

21
00:01:47,316 --> 00:01:54,240
Every cent came from smuggling
people in refrigerated units.

22
00:01:54,323 --> 00:01:58,369
Divino Verona ordered
when to move the money.

23
00:01:58,452 --> 00:02:00,287
I just followed orders.

24
00:02:00,371 --> 00:02:03,207
Defense,
your cross-examination.

25
00:02:03,290 --> 00:02:04,458
Your Honor...

26
00:02:05,417 --> 00:02:08,754
I would like to conduct
the cross-examination myself.

27
00:02:12,007 --> 00:02:15,636
Pearl or Rita, whatever your name is.

28
00:02:16,804 --> 00:02:21,058
Didn't you have
the passwords and the systems?

29
00:02:21,141 --> 00:02:22,852
- Is that right?
- Yes.

30
00:02:22,935 --> 00:02:25,229
Did you see my wife at the pier

31
00:02:25,312 --> 00:02:28,065
giving orders or holding the logbook?

32
00:02:28,148 --> 00:02:30,150
- No, but she knew--
- So no.

33
00:02:30,234 --> 00:02:31,068
Your Honor,

34
00:02:31,151 --> 00:02:34,363
I would like to question
the credibility of this witness.

35
00:02:34,446 --> 00:02:36,115
She's a polluted source.

36
00:02:36,198 --> 00:02:37,908
A prime suspect in the kidnapping,

37
00:02:37,992 --> 00:02:40,494
spinning tales for immunity.

38
00:02:40,578 --> 00:02:43,122
Objection, Your Honor!
Character assassination!

39
00:02:43,205 --> 00:02:45,583
Overruled. Proceed.

40
00:02:46,166 --> 00:02:51,130
Pearl, since you were
the one with the technical expertise,

41
00:02:51,213 --> 00:02:55,593
didn't you set up
the dummy accounts for yourself?

42
00:02:55,676 --> 00:02:59,013
And now that you've been caught,
you're trying to frame us?

43
00:02:59,096 --> 00:03:01,265
No! That's not true.

44
00:03:01,348 --> 00:03:04,184
I was just following your orders.
It was all your doing!

45
00:03:04,268 --> 00:03:06,854
Your Honor,
I would like to have that strike out

46
00:03:06,937 --> 00:03:10,232
for it is purely self-serving
and argumentative.

47
00:03:10,316 --> 00:03:14,778
Out of the billions of pesos
that passed through those accounts,

48
00:03:14,862 --> 00:03:17,323
is there a single bank document
bearing my signature?

49
00:03:17,406 --> 00:03:19,116
Any recording of my voice?

50
00:03:19,575 --> 00:03:20,409
Nothing.

51
00:03:20,492 --> 00:03:25,205
On paper and in the digital trail,
your name is the only one that appears.

52
00:03:25,289 --> 00:03:28,334
You are the architect of your own crimes,

53
00:03:28,417 --> 00:03:30,836
and you're just looking for a scapegoat.

54
00:03:30,920 --> 00:03:34,340
The burden of proof lies with the accuser.

55
00:03:34,423 --> 00:03:39,011
And so far, the only person "on paper"

56
00:03:39,553 --> 00:03:40,804
is you.

57
00:03:48,395 --> 00:03:51,315
Your Honor, I have no further questions

58
00:03:51,398 --> 00:03:56,070
for this polluted,
intellectually bankrupt,

59
00:03:56,153 --> 00:03:59,615
credibility-drained mess of a source.

60
00:04:14,004 --> 00:04:15,130
Be careful.

61
00:04:16,966 --> 00:04:17,967
How's Boss?

62
00:04:18,050 --> 00:04:20,511
Divino is acting as his own lawyer.

63
00:04:20,594 --> 00:04:23,180
Divino's good at twisting the truth.

64
00:04:24,056 --> 00:04:26,892
He can turn things around,
not just against your mother...

65
00:04:26,976 --> 00:04:27,893
but against all of us.

66
00:04:30,187 --> 00:04:31,605


67
00:04:31,939 --> 00:04:34,733


68
00:04:35,943 --> 00:04:37,194


69
00:04:37,277 --> 00:04:38,237


70
00:04:38,529 --> 00:04:39,738
Hello?

71
00:04:39,822 --> 00:04:41,573
Hello? This is Ronnie.

72
00:04:41,657 --> 00:04:43,742
Ronnie? What made you call?

73
00:04:44,868 --> 00:04:46,495
Are you mad at me

74
00:04:46,578 --> 00:04:49,665
because I alerted Judge Divino
and his family the other night?

75
00:04:51,083 --> 00:04:52,459
Did Teo ask you to call me?

76
00:04:52,543 --> 00:04:55,546
No. I'm actually calling about Raya.

77
00:04:55,629 --> 00:04:57,798
She's not answering my calls. Is she okay?

78
00:04:57,881 --> 00:05:00,551
Just stop forcing it, Ronnie.

79
00:05:00,634 --> 00:05:04,763
Judge Divino and Ma'am Katarina
don't like you because of Teo.

80
00:05:04,847 --> 00:05:06,348
Just leave them be.

81
00:05:06,432 --> 00:05:08,642
You've just made the situation worse.

82
00:05:09,685 --> 00:05:11,937
I'm hanging up now. I'm busy. Bye.

83
00:05:14,648 --> 00:05:16,859

The nerve of that piece of shit!

84
00:05:25,451 --> 00:05:27,036
- Mike.
Yeah?

85
00:05:28,120 --> 00:05:29,371

I just want to ask something.

86
00:05:30,289 --> 00:05:32,416
I saw a file in the hard drive.

87
00:05:32,499 --> 00:05:35,127
A file about Roger Cabrel?

88
00:05:36,003 --> 00:05:37,004
Who is he?

89
00:05:37,087 --> 00:05:38,964
He was the only one with a picture there.

90
00:05:39,048 --> 00:05:40,257
He was with a little girl.

91
00:05:40,340 --> 00:05:42,092
The picture had the name "Rachel" on it.

92
00:05:42,843 --> 00:05:44,011
She looks like Gem.

93
00:05:46,930 --> 00:05:48,932
- Where?
Here.

94
00:05:54,438 --> 00:05:55,856
That's me...

95
00:05:55,939 --> 00:05:57,107
What?

96
00:06:01,445 --> 00:06:03,030
This was in Casablanca.

97
00:06:07,242 --> 00:06:08,410
I can't...

98
00:06:08,911 --> 00:06:11,163
I can't even remember my mother's name.

99
00:06:11,747 --> 00:06:12,998
Or what she looked like.

100
00:06:13,582 --> 00:06:16,293
I was only five years old
when they left me.

101
00:06:17,836 --> 00:06:20,798
Then I was passed around
from one caretaker to another.

102
00:06:28,972 --> 00:06:31,391
Is Roger Cabrel my father?

103
00:06:34,061 --> 00:06:35,646
And my mother...

104
00:06:37,356 --> 00:06:38,607
who is she?

105
00:06:38,690 --> 00:06:41,568


106
00:06:45,030 --> 00:06:47,074
Your mother and father have been gone
for a long time.

107
00:06:48,575 --> 00:06:50,160
It's better if Pearl explains everything
to you herself.

108
00:06:50,244 --> 00:06:52,162
But I'm asking you!

109
00:06:53,622 --> 00:06:55,124
I don't know the whole story, Gem.

110
00:06:55,207 --> 00:06:56,208


111
00:06:58,877 --> 00:07:01,380
-
You should talk to Pearl.

112
00:07:03,507 --> 00:07:05,425
Why did you hide this from me?

113
00:07:07,427 --> 00:07:08,595
Why?

114
00:07:10,681 --> 00:07:11,598
Gem.

115
00:07:22,985 --> 00:07:24,069
Gem.

116
00:07:26,405 --> 00:07:27,573
Rachel.

117
00:07:30,033 --> 00:07:31,785
Rachel is my real name.

118
00:07:33,912 --> 00:07:36,331
I spent so long
trying to find out who I was...

119
00:07:38,584 --> 00:07:41,920
Turns out the answer
was in a hard drive all this time.

120
00:07:50,554 --> 00:07:52,139
Roger Cabrel is my father.

121
00:07:53,223 --> 00:07:54,725
But what about my mother?

122
00:07:56,685 --> 00:07:57,936
Who is she?

123
00:08:00,063 --> 00:08:01,315
Where are they?

124
00:08:02,566 --> 00:08:04,818
Are they in jail? Are they hiding?

125
00:08:04,902 --> 00:08:06,904
Did Mama Nadia know?

126
00:08:08,113 --> 00:08:09,781
Teo, I have so many questions.

127
00:08:11,241 --> 00:08:12,910
Gem, I don't know the answers.

128
00:08:13,952 --> 00:08:15,454
But Mike's right.

129
00:08:16,830 --> 00:08:18,665
Only my mother can give you the answers.

130
00:08:18,749 --> 00:08:21,043
But she's under witness protection!

131
00:08:21,126 --> 00:08:23,921
We only have five minutes
to talk to her on the phone.

132
00:08:24,004 --> 00:08:25,756
And we can't just go outside.

133
00:08:25,839 --> 00:08:28,383
She'll be out soon.
We can talk to her about this.

134
00:08:28,467 --> 00:08:30,552
But I can't wait any longer.

135
00:08:30,636 --> 00:08:31,803
Gem...

136
00:08:32,304 --> 00:08:35,057
I know you've always dreamed
of finding the truth

137
00:08:35,140 --> 00:08:38,060
about yourself and your family.

138
00:08:38,894 --> 00:08:41,146
Now, we have a chance to do that.

139
00:08:43,357 --> 00:08:45,025
But you don't have to rush things.

140
00:08:45,108 --> 00:08:47,903
I want answers now, Teo!

141
00:08:47,986 --> 00:08:51,156
I've been waiting all my life.
I can't wait any longer.

142
00:08:51,240 --> 00:08:53,575
You can wait. I'm sure you can.

143
00:08:53,659 --> 00:08:56,828
I promise we'll do everything we can
to piece it all together.

144
00:08:56,912 --> 00:08:58,705
Tomorrow, I'll go to Mama--

145
00:08:58,789 --> 00:09:00,040
I'm coming with you.

146
00:09:09,466 --> 00:09:11,635


147
00:09:22,271 --> 00:09:24,356
Papa said you should call Ronnie.

148
00:09:24,439 --> 00:09:25,816
Have him meet with Raya.

149
00:09:25,899 --> 00:09:27,651
Are you sure, sir?

150
00:09:27,734 --> 00:09:30,404
Do I look like I'm not? Just do it, okay?

151
00:09:54,052 --> 00:09:55,470
What are you doing here?

152
00:09:55,554 --> 00:09:57,055
I just want to explain, Raya.

153
00:09:57,139 --> 00:09:58,598
You were the only one who knew

154
00:09:58,682 --> 00:10:01,310
that I would be going home
to my parents that night.

155
00:10:02,519 --> 00:10:04,354
You're the only person
who could've told Teo.

156
00:10:04,438 --> 00:10:05,939
I didn't know they would do that.

157
00:10:06,356 --> 00:10:08,525
That was their chance
to bring our family down,

158
00:10:08,608 --> 00:10:10,610
and you were well aware of their plan,

159
00:10:10,694 --> 00:10:12,612
but you didn't protect me.

160
00:10:14,990 --> 00:10:16,491
My parents confronted me.

161
00:10:19,119 --> 00:10:20,954
But I didn't throw you under the bus.

162
00:10:22,289 --> 00:10:24,708
I didn't tell them where you are hiding.

163
00:10:25,876 --> 00:10:27,294
I didn't talk.

164
00:10:27,878 --> 00:10:29,046
For you.

165
00:10:30,297 --> 00:10:31,798
Because I loved you.

166
00:10:33,425 --> 00:10:36,261
Raya, wait. I'm sorry.

167
00:10:36,345 --> 00:10:37,346
No.

168
00:10:38,138 --> 00:10:40,974
Enough.
I won't listen to you anymore.

169
00:10:41,058 --> 00:10:43,643
I'll never betray my family again.

170
00:10:44,728 --> 00:10:46,063
Raya.

171
00:11:15,342 --> 00:11:18,345
Due to the "ignorant spouse" defense

172
00:11:18,428 --> 00:11:21,640
and the affidavit of responsibility

173
00:11:21,723 --> 00:11:23,975
submitted by the defense,

174
00:11:24,059 --> 00:11:29,773
the court has not yet seen strong evidence

175
00:11:29,856 --> 00:11:34,903
that Katarina Verona was involved

176
00:11:34,986 --> 00:11:37,322
in the operation and decision-making

177
00:11:37,406 --> 00:11:40,158
of the illegal accounts.

178
00:11:40,242 --> 00:11:43,745
While the affidavit is being verified,

179
00:11:43,829 --> 00:11:47,666
the court allows Katarina Verona

180
00:11:47,749 --> 00:11:49,126
to post bail.

181
00:11:51,044 --> 00:11:55,090
However, concerning Divino Verona,

182
00:11:55,173 --> 00:12:00,595
the court finds strong evidence

183
00:12:00,679 --> 00:12:05,684
of his direct involvement
in human trafficking

184
00:12:05,767 --> 00:12:08,478
and large-scale money laundering.

185
00:12:08,562 --> 00:12:10,564
Owing to the gravity of the offenses

186
00:12:10,647 --> 00:12:14,151
and the flight risk he poses,

187
00:12:14,234 --> 00:12:17,237
the court has denied

188
00:12:17,320 --> 00:12:20,323
his petition for bail.

189
00:12:20,407 --> 00:12:21,908
No, Divino.

190
00:12:21,992 --> 00:12:23,410
- I won't leave you.
- He shall remain

191
00:12:23,493 --> 00:12:28,832
in custody pending the duration
of the trial.

192
00:12:28,915 --> 00:12:30,584
Court is adjourned.

193
00:12:32,544 --> 00:12:36,131
I won't leave you!
I'm not going to leave without you!

194
00:12:36,214 --> 00:12:37,883
Katarina, this has nothing to do
with you anymore.

195
00:12:37,966 --> 00:12:39,050
Just go, just go.

196
00:12:39,134 --> 00:12:41,386
- I can't!
- I'll handle this.

197
00:12:42,471 --> 00:12:44,681
- No...
- We will get you out.

198
00:12:44,764 --> 00:12:47,434
Don't just focus
on getting me out, Ace.

199
00:12:48,059 --> 00:12:49,895
Look for Teo and the others.

200
00:12:49,978 --> 00:12:53,148
Find Pearl's new safehouse!

201
00:12:53,231 --> 00:12:56,151
They will all pay for their betrayals.

202
00:12:56,234 --> 00:12:58,320
Every single one of them!

203
00:13:14,461 --> 00:13:15,629
Dad!

204
00:13:17,005 --> 00:13:18,340
Here are the ingredients
you asked me to buy.

205
00:13:18,423 --> 00:13:20,008
Well, that's good.

206
00:13:20,592 --> 00:13:23,345
I thought I'd be cooking our food
at midnight!

207
00:13:23,428 --> 00:13:25,722
Dad and I are starving, Ronnie!

208
00:13:25,805 --> 00:13:27,516
Where did you go?

209
00:13:28,850 --> 00:13:30,519
I just had to stop by somewhere
real quick.

210
00:13:30,602 --> 00:13:31,770
Ronnie,

211
00:13:31,853 --> 00:13:33,855
you shouldn't be roaming around at night.

212
00:13:33,939 --> 00:13:36,191
Especially if it's not necessary.

213
00:13:36,274 --> 00:13:37,359
Remember...

214
00:13:37,442 --> 00:13:39,945
you have a price on your head.

215
00:13:45,534 --> 00:13:46,952
Haven't you slept yet?

216
00:13:48,787 --> 00:13:51,456
- It's already morning.
- Just getting some fresh air.

217
00:13:52,415 --> 00:13:53,750
And you? Why are you still awake?

218
00:13:53,833 --> 00:13:55,585
I wanted to visit my mother.

219
00:13:57,087 --> 00:13:59,589
But I remembered her guards are strict.

220
00:13:59,673 --> 00:14:01,716
She's with the police.

221
00:14:01,800 --> 00:14:04,094
They're personally looking out for her.

222
00:14:04,511 --> 00:14:05,845
She's safer there.

223
00:14:09,015 --> 00:14:10,475
Divino took the blame for everything

224
00:14:10,559 --> 00:14:12,269
just to keep Katarina
from being dragged into it.

225
00:14:12,352 --> 00:14:14,771
But he won't be able
to escape those charges.

226
00:14:14,854 --> 00:14:17,857
And I don't believe
Katarina is just an innocent wife.

227
00:14:17,941 --> 00:14:19,651
She played a big role in the organization.

228
00:14:19,734 --> 00:14:20,652
I know.

229
00:14:20,735 --> 00:14:23,321
Maybe we could find evidence in the files

230
00:14:23,405 --> 00:14:25,323
that would prove
that she knows everything.

231
00:14:25,407 --> 00:14:27,993
It looks like Divino prepared
for this kind of scenario.

232
00:14:28,076 --> 00:14:30,954
Katarina's name isn't anywhere
in those files.

233
00:14:31,037 --> 00:14:33,290
We'll find it, Teo.

234
00:14:34,749 --> 00:14:37,377
You go on and rest.
I'll be right behind you.

235
00:14:53,518 --> 00:14:55,186
Teo!

236
00:15:00,984 --> 00:15:02,694
Teo!

237
00:15:06,823 --> 00:15:07,824
Gem?

238
00:15:10,827 --> 00:15:11,870
Hey!

239
00:15:12,621 --> 00:15:13,872
Hey!

240
00:15:19,169 --> 00:15:20,086
Gem!

241
00:15:23,298 --> 00:15:24,966
Gem!

242
00:17:33,845 --> 00:17:34,929
Let's go.

243
00:17:35,013 --> 00:17:36,931
Let's see if they're by the river.

244
00:17:49,360 --> 00:17:50,361
Teo...

245
00:17:54,282 --> 00:17:55,617
we're on...

246
00:17:56,659 --> 00:17:58,077
Ignacio Highway.

247
00:17:58,620 --> 00:18:00,288
Near the Salumpad River.

248
00:18:00,371 --> 00:18:01,706
Please, hurry.

249
00:18:05,376 --> 00:18:06,961
They're already at the river.

250
00:18:10,465 --> 00:18:11,883
Where are you taking me?

251
00:18:14,260 --> 00:18:16,387
Where are you taking me?

252
00:18:19,974 --> 00:18:21,559
Let me go!

253
00:18:31,277 --> 00:18:32,946
Let me go!

254
00:19:30,962 --> 00:19:33,214
Quit it!

255
00:20:00,700 --> 00:20:02,201
This is it, Gem.

256
00:20:06,956 --> 00:20:08,958
My justice.

257
00:20:09,042 --> 00:20:11,294
Justice for my own child that you killed!

258
00:20:12,003 --> 00:20:15,256
If Teo were the father,
would you have been more careful?

259
00:20:18,009 --> 00:20:19,427
Why, Gem?

260
00:20:19,510 --> 00:20:21,220
All I ever did was love you!

261
00:20:23,222 --> 00:20:24,390
But now...

262
00:20:26,601 --> 00:20:29,520
...I'm going to kill you.

263
00:20:49,832 --> 00:20:51,501
Come to think of it...

264
00:20:51,584 --> 00:20:54,837
...it's better for you to be
alive when I throw you into the river.

265
00:20:54,921 --> 00:20:58,466
So feel the struggle of fighting
for every single breath to stay alive.

266
00:20:58,549 --> 00:21:00,802
So you will surely suffer.

267
00:21:01,260 --> 00:21:02,762
But what now, Gem?

268
00:21:03,805 --> 00:21:06,391
There is nothing you can do but die.

269
00:21:10,770 --> 00:21:11,688
Throw her in the river!

270
00:21:57,900 --> 00:21:59,736
Come on! Do it!

271
00:22:36,606 --> 00:22:37,648
Gem!

272
00:22:43,071 --> 00:22:44,113
Gem!

273
00:23:53,558 --> 00:23:55,643
Gem! Gem!

274
00:24:03,484 --> 00:24:04,485
Gem!

275
00:24:07,864 --> 00:24:09,365
Gem! Gem!

276
00:24:13,244 --> 00:24:14,912
Don't worry. I'm right here.

277
00:24:14,996 --> 00:24:17,748
Teo...

278
00:24:23,504 --> 00:24:24,839
Can you move?

279
00:24:25,256 --> 00:24:27,341
- Wait here. I'll get some help.
- No! Don't!

280
00:24:27,425 --> 00:24:28,759
They'll find you!

281
00:24:28,843 --> 00:24:30,136
I don't care.

282
00:24:30,219 --> 00:24:32,597
We have to get you to a hospital!

283
00:24:33,598 --> 00:24:35,600
- Wait here.
- Te-- Teo!

284
00:24:44,233 --> 00:24:48,196
Considering
the behavior of the accused in court

285
00:24:48,279 --> 00:24:51,324
and the psychiatric findings
submitted by the defense,

286
00:24:51,407 --> 00:24:55,661
and the court finds sufficient basis
to question

287
00:24:55,745 --> 00:24:59,207
the mental competency
of the accused to stand trial.

288
00:24:59,290 --> 00:25:01,584
Accordingly, the court orders

289
00:25:01,667 --> 00:25:04,712
that the accused, Alexander Ace Verona,
be committed

290
00:25:04,795 --> 00:25:08,466
to the Philippine Metropolitan
Forensic Ward and Asylum

291
00:25:08,549 --> 00:25:12,511
for comprehensive
psychiatric evaluation and treatment.

292
00:25:12,970 --> 00:25:15,973
Proceedings in this case
is hereby suspended

293
00:25:16,057 --> 00:25:20,269
until the court receives the findings
of the psychiatric examination.

294
00:25:20,353 --> 00:25:21,771
Court is adjourned.

295
00:25:21,854 --> 00:25:25,024
Get me out of here...

296
00:25:25,107 --> 00:25:27,360
- I don't want to be here!
- Ace... Ace...

297
00:25:39,372 --> 00:25:40,456
Ma!

298
00:25:41,207 --> 00:25:42,291
Ma!

299
00:25:46,504 --> 00:25:47,505
Ma.

300
00:25:59,267 --> 00:26:00,518
What is it, Ma?

301
00:26:00,601 --> 00:26:02,770
Did Attorney Gomez approve your request?

302
00:26:03,229 --> 00:26:05,231
Since Divino and Ace are now imprisoned,

303
00:26:05,314 --> 00:26:07,525
at least it's safer now.

304
00:26:07,608 --> 00:26:09,193
They allowed me to go home.

305
00:26:09,277 --> 00:26:13,155
But they assigned
a 24-hour security team to be certain.

306
00:26:13,239 --> 00:26:15,408
"At least," eh?

307
00:26:15,491 --> 00:26:19,078
So that means
we're still not completely safe.

308
00:26:41,517 --> 00:26:42,685
Gem...

309
00:26:46,147 --> 00:26:48,566
We need to talk about something.

310
00:26:48,983 --> 00:26:50,026
About Roger.

311
00:26:50,443 --> 00:26:52,069
My father.

312
00:26:52,153 --> 00:26:54,947
Roger is among those I helped escape
back then.

313
00:27:03,039 --> 00:27:05,124
I never expected that...

314
00:27:05,207 --> 00:27:09,045
our paths would cross
when you asked for my help before.

315
00:27:09,128 --> 00:27:11,213
How did you know
that I'm Roger's daughter?

316
00:27:12,256 --> 00:27:13,674
That I'm Rachel?

317
00:27:13,758 --> 00:27:14,717
Mike...

318
00:27:15,468 --> 00:27:17,553
met you when you were a kid,

319
00:27:17,636 --> 00:27:20,639
and your father knew
that Nadia took care of you.

320
00:27:23,142 --> 00:27:24,894
But he didn't look for me.

321
00:27:26,145 --> 00:27:27,813
I looked for him for so long.

322
00:27:27,897 --> 00:27:29,774
Didn't he even think about me?

323
00:27:29,857 --> 00:27:31,692
Your father is a scoundrel.

324
00:27:31,776 --> 00:27:33,986
He's the executioner in an organization.

325
00:27:34,070 --> 00:27:36,572
He chose to ignore your existence.

326
00:27:37,114 --> 00:27:39,367
Maybe he chose to do so
in order to protect you.

327
00:27:41,160 --> 00:27:43,329
You still kept it from me.

328
00:27:43,412 --> 00:27:46,248
I wasn't sure if knowing
would do you any good.

329
00:27:46,332 --> 00:27:49,502
You kept everything from me, even this?

330
00:27:54,256 --> 00:27:55,925
Please forgive me.

331
00:27:58,052 --> 00:28:01,806
If you want to find your family,
I'll help you.

332
00:28:36,882 --> 00:28:37,967
Hello?

333
00:28:39,635 --> 00:28:40,803
Anybody home?

334
00:28:47,768 --> 00:28:50,104
Who are you? Can I help you?

335
00:29:00,448 --> 00:29:01,699
I am Rachel.

336
00:29:03,284 --> 00:29:05,619
The daughter you left in Morocco.

337
00:29:11,208 --> 00:29:12,960
I can't remember everything.

338
00:29:13,043 --> 00:29:15,796
I can't even remember my mother's face.

339
00:29:19,341 --> 00:29:20,843
Or yours.

340
00:29:21,343 --> 00:29:24,597
Your mother, Fatima... died.

341
00:29:26,599 --> 00:29:28,601
But why did you leave me?

342
00:29:30,144 --> 00:29:31,645
Why did you abandon me?

343
00:29:31,729 --> 00:29:32,980
Why wouldn't I?

344
00:29:34,899 --> 00:29:37,151
I'm not a good person!

345
00:29:37,234 --> 00:29:39,862
I'm not worthy enough
for you to look for me!

346
00:29:39,945 --> 00:29:42,031
You shouldn't have looked for me!

347
00:29:42,114 --> 00:29:43,699
I shouldn't have?

348
00:29:46,660 --> 00:29:49,747
You don't know what I've been through!

349
00:29:51,999 --> 00:29:54,585
I've done things I shouldn't have.

350
00:29:57,671 --> 00:29:59,089
I'm a criminal.

351
00:29:59,965 --> 00:30:01,717
A cheater.

352
00:30:01,800 --> 00:30:03,219
A thief.

353
00:30:04,428 --> 00:30:05,930
And it's all because of you.

354
00:30:06,847 --> 00:30:08,182
I know that...

355
00:30:11,602 --> 00:30:13,687
...you can never forgive me, but...

356
00:30:16,690 --> 00:30:18,108
I hope...

357
00:30:18,192 --> 00:30:20,027
you forgive me for this.

358
00:30:44,635 --> 00:30:45,761
Here.

359
00:30:50,766 --> 00:30:52,434
That's you, Rachel.

360
00:30:53,978 --> 00:30:55,312
My daughter...

361
00:30:58,899 --> 00:31:00,025
Here's more.

362
00:31:14,873 --> 00:31:16,709
Your baptismal and birth certificates.

363
00:31:19,670 --> 00:31:21,839
This proves you were born here.

364
00:31:50,868 --> 00:31:52,036
Raya.

365
00:31:56,165 --> 00:31:57,750
I'm sorry, Ronnie.

366
00:31:59,585 --> 00:32:01,670
I had nowhere else to go.

367
00:32:05,799 --> 00:32:07,134
I'm exhausted.

368
00:32:08,719 --> 00:32:09,803
Raya...

369
00:32:11,722 --> 00:32:13,641
I'm sorry.

370
00:32:14,683 --> 00:32:17,269
I used to blame you
for everything that happened.

371
00:32:18,145 --> 00:32:19,980
But when I discovered the truth,

372
00:32:20,064 --> 00:32:23,567
especially after learning
about the people my brother killed

373
00:32:26,195 --> 00:32:30,449
and the victims
of my family's illegal recruitment scheme,

374
00:32:31,784 --> 00:32:33,452
I felt ashamed.

375
00:32:33,535 --> 00:32:35,287
Not only for what happened to you,

376
00:32:35,829 --> 00:32:37,873
but also for the families of the victims.

377
00:32:41,168 --> 00:32:42,753
It's so hard.

378
00:32:43,921 --> 00:32:46,840
I have to live with what my family did.

379
00:32:46,924 --> 00:32:50,094
We can't keep turning a blind eye
to what's happening.

380
00:32:51,261 --> 00:32:52,513
Even though they're your family, Raya.

381
00:32:52,596 --> 00:32:54,682
I know, and I'm sorry.

382
00:32:55,683 --> 00:32:57,267
But I have nobody left now.

383
00:32:59,353 --> 00:33:02,189
Everything that I am is now a disgrace.

384
00:33:04,817 --> 00:33:06,985
I have nothing
to be proud of anymore, Ronnie.

385
00:33:14,618 --> 00:33:17,621
And I'm afraid I'll lose you too.

386
00:33:20,416 --> 00:33:21,417
No.

387
00:33:22,960 --> 00:33:24,962
I'm not going anywhere, Raya.

388
00:33:25,421 --> 00:33:28,424
I can't promise I'll walk away from Teo...

389
00:33:29,883 --> 00:33:31,719
because he is my family.

390
00:33:32,261 --> 00:33:36,432
But despite everything that's happened,
I won't let you go.

391
00:33:38,517 --> 00:33:40,018
I'm not going to leave you.

392
00:34:45,167 --> 00:34:46,502
At last!

393
00:34:51,715 --> 00:34:55,636
Veronas don't just vanish without a fight.

394
00:34:55,719 --> 00:34:58,806
We still have influence and power.

395
00:35:00,098 --> 00:35:02,434
The lesson learned, Raya, is...

396
00:35:02,518 --> 00:35:04,102
you have to plan ahead.

397
00:35:04,186 --> 00:35:07,731
And you have to treat everyone else
as your enemy.

398
00:35:07,815 --> 00:35:10,150
That's why your dad planned ahead

399
00:35:10,234 --> 00:35:13,487
and made sure
that everyone would fall...

400
00:35:13,570 --> 00:35:17,324
...once they turned
their backs on us and betrayed us.

401
00:35:18,492 --> 00:35:21,662
I was able to pull this off
with the help of some...

402
00:35:22,663 --> 00:35:23,831
friends.

403
00:35:25,082 --> 00:35:30,504
Soon,
we will be able to start our new lives.

404
00:35:30,587 --> 00:35:31,672
We?

405
00:35:33,674 --> 00:35:35,092
But what about Ace?

406
00:36:34,192 --> 00:36:36,361
They will definitely go into hiding.

407
00:36:37,112 --> 00:36:41,950
But they have nowhere else to hide
in the Philippines.

408
00:36:42,034 --> 00:36:44,494
They were placed under a travel ban.

409
00:36:44,578 --> 00:36:46,496
They can't leave the country.

410
00:36:47,456 --> 00:36:50,459
It'll be hard, but it's not impossible.

411
00:36:50,542 --> 00:36:54,463
I'm an ordinary person,
but I was able to do it.

412
00:36:54,546 --> 00:36:56,465
And they have connections.

413
00:36:56,548 --> 00:37:00,302
And a ton of money. They can easily
bribe their way out of here.

414
00:37:01,762 --> 00:37:05,599
Most of their money
is in the offshore account I control.

415
00:37:06,058 --> 00:37:09,728
Which they still can't access at all.

416
00:37:11,855 --> 00:37:13,857
Eric took care of everything.

417
00:37:15,192 --> 00:37:18,487
The yacht will take us to a remote island.

418
00:37:18,570 --> 00:37:20,322
We'll stay there for a few weeks

419
00:37:20,405 --> 00:37:24,034
before they pick us up one by one
to board a cruise to Darwin, Australia.

420
00:37:24,117 --> 00:37:27,287
- We won't board the cruise together?
- No.

421
00:37:27,371 --> 00:37:29,957
We'll be less conspicuous
if we don't travel together.

422
00:37:30,040 --> 00:37:31,792
The cruise is for 21 nights.

423
00:37:31,875 --> 00:37:35,462
They'll keep going in circles
trying to find us the entire time.

424
00:37:35,545 --> 00:37:37,297
But they won't find us.

425
00:37:37,798 --> 00:37:41,635
I never imagined
that our lives would be like this.

426
00:37:42,344 --> 00:37:45,472
It took quite some time to build all this.

427
00:37:45,555 --> 00:37:47,182
The Verona name.

428
00:37:47,265 --> 00:37:49,309
The respect,

429
00:37:49,393 --> 00:37:51,603
the power, and then now this?

430
00:37:51,687 --> 00:37:52,729
I know.

431
00:37:53,647 --> 00:37:55,732
But we have no other choice.

432
00:37:56,483 --> 00:38:00,320
We have to be discreet.
The authorities are after us.

433
00:38:00,988 --> 00:38:03,407
We just have to leave
so we can fight another day.

434
00:38:03,490 --> 00:38:05,409
We still have the money.

435
00:38:05,492 --> 00:38:06,868
In dollars.

436
00:38:06,952 --> 00:38:08,537
Don't panic.

437
00:38:08,620 --> 00:38:11,289
Yes, and we also have
emergency passports in the vault.

438
00:38:11,748 --> 00:38:14,251
When are we leaving?
I can ask Larajean to pick them up for us.

439
00:38:14,334 --> 00:38:17,212
No!
I still don't trust that girl.

440
00:38:17,295 --> 00:38:18,213
Do we have a choice?

441
00:38:18,296 --> 00:38:20,257
I'll have Eric do it.

442
00:38:20,340 --> 00:38:23,343
Well, I think that's a better choice.

443
00:38:23,427 --> 00:38:25,971
Enough with Larajean, Ace!

444
00:38:26,054 --> 00:38:29,224
Don't tell me you have plans for her.

445
00:38:30,225 --> 00:38:32,978
Well, so what? Do you?

446
00:38:35,105 --> 00:38:36,523
Of course not. No.

447
00:38:37,941 --> 00:38:39,192
Good.

448
00:38:39,276 --> 00:38:42,654
That woman
hasn't gotten into your head yet.

449
00:38:42,738 --> 00:38:45,365
She is so manipulative.

450
00:38:45,449 --> 00:38:47,284
For a while, I thought

451
00:38:47,367 --> 00:38:49,411
you might have fallen
for the wrong woman again.

452
00:38:49,494 --> 00:38:51,329
She was just a plaything, okay, Ma?

453
00:38:51,413 --> 00:38:54,207
A caregiver. A dumb blonde.

454
00:38:54,291 --> 00:38:57,335
But I'll admit,
she did entertain me for a while.

455
00:38:58,879 --> 00:39:01,214
Okay. Glad that's settled.

456
00:39:01,298 --> 00:39:06,386
Because whatever we do next,
I don't want anyone else involved.

457
00:39:07,262 --> 00:39:08,597
Just me...

458
00:39:08,680 --> 00:39:11,767
...you, you, and you.

459
00:39:13,643 --> 00:39:15,228
No one else.

460
00:39:25,405 --> 00:39:29,451
Pearl, the funds in Divino Verona's
offshore account have been transferred.

461
00:39:29,534 --> 00:39:32,162
They're in the hands
of the right people now.

462
00:39:32,245 --> 00:39:33,747
Thank you for your cooperation.

463
00:39:34,498 --> 00:39:37,918
Thank you for the protection
and assistance, Colonel.

464
00:39:38,460 --> 00:39:40,796
And because of your help and cooperation,

465
00:39:40,879 --> 00:39:44,007
we've taken down a large syndicate
of human smugglers.

466
00:39:44,091 --> 00:39:46,551
This is a major victory. Thank you.

467
00:39:47,886 --> 00:39:51,973
Colonel, Teo and Gem have made a decision.

468
00:39:52,891 --> 00:39:55,977
So has the rest of our family.

469
00:39:56,937 --> 00:39:58,688
Let's push through with the plan.

470
00:40:00,857 --> 00:40:01,900
The rest of your family,

471
00:40:01,983 --> 00:40:05,612
Ronnie, Alonzo, and Issay
will be put in a safehouse

472
00:40:05,695 --> 00:40:07,614
while all of this is happening.

473
00:40:07,697 --> 00:40:10,784
You have to follow orders to the letter
to ensure your safety.

474
00:40:11,701 --> 00:40:13,370
They're aware, Colonel.

475
00:40:13,954 --> 00:40:17,374
We need to make sure
our target arrives according to plan.

476
00:40:20,961 --> 00:40:21,962
Colonel.

477
00:40:22,838 --> 00:40:24,172
Perfect timing.

478
00:40:26,466 --> 00:40:27,384
Larajean.

479
00:40:27,467 --> 00:40:28,468
Teo.

480
00:40:30,178 --> 00:40:32,848
I just called to...

481
00:40:32,931 --> 00:40:33,932
apologize

482
00:40:34,015 --> 00:40:38,103
for all the things I've done to you.

483
00:40:39,437 --> 00:40:40,689
To all of you.

484
00:40:40,772 --> 00:40:43,066
I wasn't expecting this, Larajean.

485
00:40:43,150 --> 00:40:46,069
I don't think
I'm ready to forgive you yet.

486
00:40:47,362 --> 00:40:49,698
What you did to me, to all of us...

487
00:40:50,282 --> 00:40:51,366
is unforgivable.

488
00:40:52,117 --> 00:40:54,202
Someone almost died.

489
00:40:54,286 --> 00:40:56,746
I know.

490
00:40:56,830 --> 00:40:57,998
That's why...

491
00:40:58,915 --> 00:41:01,084
I want to make things right.

492
00:41:02,627 --> 00:41:04,045
<i>In any way...</i>

493
00:41:04,129 --> 00:41:07,132
<i>in whatever way I can.</i>

494
00:41:07,841 --> 00:41:11,845
So I can start anew.

495
00:41:13,513 --> 00:41:14,681
<i>Teo...</i>

496
00:41:15,307 --> 00:41:16,725
<i>I'm pregnant.</i>

497
00:41:19,352 --> 00:41:20,687
Ace is the father.

498
00:41:24,524 --> 00:41:26,526
I was taken advantage of again.

499
00:41:28,486 --> 00:41:31,656
<i>I really became an idiot</i>
<i>for the sake of ambition.</i>

500
00:41:31,740 --> 00:41:33,241
But you know what?

501
00:41:34,326 --> 00:41:37,913
This baby has given me
a reason to start over,

502
00:41:39,873 --> 00:41:45,712
to live a clean and decent life,

503
00:41:46,963 --> 00:41:48,381
<i>a quiet life,</i>

504
00:41:48,465 --> 00:41:50,800
far from the Veronas,

505
00:41:50,884 --> 00:41:55,430
who did nothing
but make me feel worthless.

506
00:41:55,513 --> 00:41:57,182
Larajean,

507
00:41:57,891 --> 00:41:59,976
how could you let them
belittle you like that?

508
00:42:00,060 --> 00:42:01,311
I know.

509
00:42:01,978 --> 00:42:03,563
But that was my choice.

510
00:42:04,439 --> 00:42:07,275
Because I wanted the glamorous life.

511
00:42:09,069 --> 00:42:12,739
Now, I'm choosing
to make things right with you.

512
00:42:16,534 --> 00:42:17,869
Teo...

513
00:42:17,953 --> 00:42:21,373
I have access to the vault
containing what's left of their money.

514
00:42:22,332 --> 00:42:27,337
<i>It contains</i>
<i>$10 million and their passports.</i>

515
00:42:27,712 --> 00:42:29,256
You can seize them and turn them over.

516
00:42:29,673 --> 00:42:32,092
Okay, I'll coordinate with the police.

517
00:42:32,175 --> 00:42:33,760
Where is this vault?

518
00:42:34,302 --> 00:42:36,972
I will send you the exact address.

519
00:42:37,055 --> 00:42:39,266
<i>I'll prepare everything.</i>

520
00:42:39,349 --> 00:42:44,646
You need to get to it as soon as possible
because the Veronas are about to flee.

521
00:43:12,799 --> 00:43:14,551
We got here just in time.

522
00:43:15,051 --> 00:43:17,470
That woman was going to steal my money.

523
00:43:18,805 --> 00:43:22,392
Go. Take this to the car.

524
00:43:53,757 --> 00:43:54,966
- I knew it!
- Judge!

525
00:43:55,050 --> 00:43:55,967
- I knew it!
- Judge! Judge!

526
00:43:56,051 --> 00:43:58,011
Please, Judge! Wait!

527
00:43:58,094 --> 00:44:00,847
Stop! No!

528
00:44:00,930 --> 00:44:02,432
Judge! Please!

529
00:44:02,515 --> 00:44:03,933
I knew it!

530
00:44:05,018 --> 00:44:06,436
You really are a thief!

531
00:44:06,519 --> 00:44:08,772
No, Judge. No.

532
00:44:08,855 --> 00:44:10,857
Ace asked me to come over.

533
00:44:10,940 --> 00:44:14,527
He asked me to prepare your things
for your departure.

534
00:44:22,911 --> 00:44:24,329
- <i>Pa?</i>
- Ace.

535
00:44:24,871 --> 00:44:27,290
I told you I'd access the vault!

536
00:44:27,374 --> 00:44:29,417
What the hell is Larajean doing here?

537
00:44:29,501 --> 00:44:30,585
What?

538
00:44:30,668 --> 00:44:32,253
I told her not to go.

539
00:44:35,131 --> 00:44:36,633
You really are a traitor!

540
00:44:47,060 --> 00:44:48,561
So I was right.

541
00:44:49,854 --> 00:44:53,942
She really was preparing
to steal our money.

542
00:44:54,401 --> 00:44:56,736
What?

543
00:44:56,820 --> 00:44:58,947
Kill that traitor, Pa!

544
00:45:03,076 --> 00:45:04,411
- Hands up!
- Hands up!

545
00:45:08,998 --> 00:45:10,166
Move it!

546
00:45:10,250 --> 00:45:12,710
Sir, come on. Let's get Larajean!

547
00:45:12,794 --> 00:45:14,754
No. Judge.

548
00:45:15,505 --> 00:45:16,464
Judge, don't!

549
00:45:16,548 --> 00:45:18,174
Judge, have mercy on me!

550
00:45:18,258 --> 00:45:19,926
Judge, please! Judge!

551
00:45:20,009 --> 00:45:21,261
Please have mercy!

552
00:45:23,680 --> 00:45:25,098
Teo!

553
00:45:56,754 --> 00:45:58,381
- Larajean.
- Teo...

554
00:45:58,465 --> 00:46:01,217
- Larajean, you've been hit.
- Let's get out of here, Teo.

555
00:46:01,301 --> 00:46:03,887
You have to save my baby.

556
00:46:14,481 --> 00:46:16,733
How dare you call me!

557
00:46:16,816 --> 00:46:20,028
Papa's blaming me for your betrayal!

558
00:46:20,111 --> 00:46:22,447
Say whatever you want, Ace.

559
00:46:22,530 --> 00:46:25,408
Because you'll never see me again.

560
00:46:26,242 --> 00:46:28,661
<i>I just called because</i>
<i>maybe you're interested to know</i>

561
00:46:28,745 --> 00:46:30,497
that Gem and Teo
are getting married today.

562
00:46:30,580 --> 00:46:31,748
What?

563
00:46:32,373 --> 00:46:35,793
<i>I wanted to go, but I'm in the hospital.</i>

564
00:46:36,544 --> 00:46:39,380
That wedding can't happen.

565
00:46:39,464 --> 00:46:40,965
Where? What time?

566
00:46:41,049 --> 00:46:41,966
Do you know?

567
00:46:42,050 --> 00:46:43,551
Pfft. Of course I know.

568
00:46:43,968 --> 00:46:45,386
But I thought...

569
00:46:45,970 --> 00:46:48,473
you and your family were leaving today.

570
00:46:48,556 --> 00:46:50,308
Don't waste this opportunity.

571
00:46:50,391 --> 00:46:51,476
I don't care!

572
00:46:51,559 --> 00:46:53,311
I have to kill them first.

573
00:46:53,394 --> 00:46:54,687
Tell me now!

574
00:47:05,406 --> 00:47:06,741
Ma! Pa!

575
00:47:07,116 --> 00:47:09,118
Ma! Pa! Ace left!

576
00:47:09,202 --> 00:47:10,119
- Huh?
- What?

577
00:47:10,203 --> 00:47:12,455
Where on earth is he going?
We're leaving in a few hours!

578
00:47:12,539 --> 00:47:13,873
The yacht is already waiting.

579
00:47:13,957 --> 00:47:17,126
He's going to Teo and Gem's wedding!
Larajean called him.

580
00:47:18,836 --> 00:47:19,921
Find out where it is.

581
00:47:26,135 --> 00:47:27,136
<i>Hello?</i>

582
00:47:27,220 --> 00:47:29,806
What nonsense did you say
to my son this time?

583
00:47:29,889 --> 00:47:31,140
Your son is an idiot!

584
00:47:31,599 --> 00:47:34,852
I'm just worried about Ace.
He should know this.

585
00:47:34,936 --> 00:47:36,062
Oh, whe--

586
00:47:36,396 --> 00:47:38,731
Where's that damn wedding? Tell me!

587
00:47:54,330 --> 00:47:55,582
This is the place.

588
00:47:55,665 --> 00:47:58,459
It looks like there aren't
that many people, sir.

589
00:47:59,043 --> 00:48:00,878
Larajean said
that it would be a small wedding.

590
00:48:00,962 --> 00:48:02,589
It's just family.

591
00:48:18,021 --> 00:48:19,939
I think those are not guests.

592
00:48:20,023 --> 00:48:22,108
Those are guards. See?

593
00:48:22,859 --> 00:48:25,862
So they sought protection
from the authorities.

594
00:48:29,741 --> 00:48:31,492
Let's just wait and see.

595
00:49:06,277 --> 00:49:07,278
Go!

596
00:49:08,655 --> 00:49:09,739
Go!

597
00:49:09,989 --> 00:49:10,990
Get over there!

598
00:49:29,509 --> 00:49:31,427
Get ready, they're here.

599
00:49:33,262 --> 00:49:34,263
Let's go.

600
00:50:14,178 --> 00:50:15,680
I loved you, Gem.

601
00:50:15,763 --> 00:50:18,516
I loved you!

602
00:50:18,599 --> 00:50:19,642
Now...

603
00:50:21,978 --> 00:50:23,479
rest in hell.

604
00:50:24,272 --> 00:50:25,356
You bitch.

605
00:50:53,718 --> 00:50:54,969
Let's go!

606
00:51:14,489 --> 00:51:16,908
Pa, we need to retreat. It's a set-up!

607
00:51:21,037 --> 00:51:22,079
Let's go!

608
00:51:30,838 --> 00:51:32,256
- Teo!
- Hide!

609
00:51:50,191 --> 00:51:51,359
Teo, run!

610
00:52:15,967 --> 00:52:17,718
Throw your guns away!

611
00:52:27,562 --> 00:52:28,896
Throw them away!

612
00:52:42,159 --> 00:52:43,578
Teo, you bastard!

613
00:52:45,246 --> 00:52:47,248
You ruined our lives!

614
00:52:47,331 --> 00:52:49,166
Your lives have long been ruined!

615
00:52:49,792 --> 00:52:52,044
Because of the many others
you've destroyed!

616
00:52:52,128 --> 00:52:53,129
What about you?

617
00:52:54,005 --> 00:52:56,007
You destroyed my life, too!

618
00:52:56,757 --> 00:52:58,259
He definitely did!

619
00:52:58,342 --> 00:53:00,595
Because you're just as evil
as your father!

620
00:53:01,137 --> 00:53:02,471
You bastards!

621
00:53:03,347 --> 00:53:04,849
Go to hell!

622
00:53:04,932 --> 00:53:05,766
Teo!

623
00:53:05,850 --> 00:53:07,602
Bastard!

624
00:53:21,407 --> 00:53:22,366
Pa!

625
00:53:23,492 --> 00:53:24,619
How dare you!

626
00:53:30,708 --> 00:53:31,709
Pa!

627
00:53:35,838 --> 00:53:37,465
This is your fault, Gem.

628
00:53:37,548 --> 00:53:40,426
I won't let them rest
as long as you're alive.

629
00:53:40,509 --> 00:53:43,262
No one in Teo's family will be spared.

630
00:53:43,346 --> 00:53:45,473
- There's nothing you can do about it.
- Gem?

631
00:53:47,391 --> 00:53:48,643
Gem?

632
00:53:48,726 --> 00:53:51,062
Gem, help is on the way, okay?

633
00:53:51,145 --> 00:53:53,272
They'll be here soon. Gem.

634
00:53:53,356 --> 00:53:54,357
Help!

635
00:53:54,941 --> 00:53:56,108
Help!

636
00:54:52,957 --> 00:54:56,585
<i>No matter how painful</i>
<i>the journey and the end are,</i>

637
00:54:56,669 --> 00:55:00,006
<i>I became complete</i>
<i>because of the love of the right person.</i>

638
00:55:00,256 --> 00:55:01,674
<i>Because of Teo.</i>

639
00:55:02,299 --> 00:55:05,636
<i>I may be gone, but I have no regrets.</i>

640
00:55:06,512 --> 00:55:09,849
<i>To grow even stronger</i>
<i>from the love we bring</i>

641
00:55:09,932 --> 00:55:12,184
<i>wherever we go, wherever we end up.</i>

642
00:55:12,268 --> 00:55:15,896
<i>A love that can never be broken by anyone.</i>

643
00:55:16,689 --> 00:55:20,026
<i>Because at the end,</i>
<i>no matter what happens,</i>

644
00:55:20,109 --> 00:55:22,778
<i>love will never be gone.</i>

645
00:55:28,200 --> 00:55:29,285
Hello, Pa?

646
00:55:29,368 --> 00:55:30,619
Hey, son!

647
00:55:31,120 --> 00:55:32,371
How's your trip going?

648
00:55:32,455 --> 00:55:35,291
I just arrived here in Japan.

649
00:55:35,374 --> 00:55:37,126
It's really gorgeous here.

650
00:55:37,209 --> 00:55:39,211
It's very soothing.

651
00:55:48,512 --> 00:55:50,264
<i>When will you be back?</i>

652
00:55:52,224 --> 00:55:53,059
Teo!

653
00:55:54,727 --> 00:55:55,811
<i>Teo?</i>

654
00:55:58,731 --> 00:55:59,732
Huh?

655
00:56:00,941 --> 00:56:03,277
<i>Teo, son! Hello?</i>

656
00:56:03,527 --> 00:56:05,780
- Good evening!
- I don't think I ever will.

657
00:56:05,863 --> 00:56:07,865
Ready to order?

658
00:56:09,450 --> 00:56:10,451
What?

659
00:56:11,368 --> 00:56:13,537
Pa, I'll just call you later, okay?

660
00:56:14,205 --> 00:56:16,040
Okay. Take care.

661
00:56:36,352 --> 00:56:37,478
How are you?

662
00:56:37,853 --> 00:56:38,896
Happy.

663
00:56:39,688 --> 00:56:41,273
Now that you're finally here.

664
00:56:44,735 --> 00:56:46,570
Didn't I tell you...

665
00:56:47,988 --> 00:56:49,573
that we'd meet again?

666
00:57:03,629 --> 00:57:05,631


667
00:57:50,926 --> 00:57:52,803
<i>You are the love of my life.</i>

668
00:57:53,470 --> 00:57:55,472
<i>And I love this life that we have.</i>

669
00:57:56,015 --> 00:57:57,433
<i>I'll do anything...</i>

670
00:57:57,766 --> 00:57:58,893
<i>everything...</i>

671
00:58:00,102 --> 00:58:02,521
<i>to protect you and our love.</i>

672
00:58:02,855 --> 00:58:04,857
I love you. Happy anniversary.

673
00:58:10,404 --> 00:58:11,530
Ben?

674
00:58:12,072 --> 00:58:14,074
<i>I woke up, and you were gone.</i>

675
00:58:14,909 --> 00:58:16,452
Ben?

676
00:58:16,535 --> 00:58:17,745
<i>Where were you?</i>

677
00:58:17,828 --> 00:58:20,789
I was here the whole time,
sleeping beside you.

678
00:58:29,340 --> 00:58:30,799
<i>Okay, so basically,</i>
<i>you're gonna pay someone</i>

679
00:58:30,883 --> 00:58:32,718
<i>from the Internet to flirt with Ben.</i>

680
00:58:32,801 --> 00:58:35,387
<i>And they'll see if he flirts back,</i>

681
00:58:35,471 --> 00:58:36,847
<i>if he denies that he's married,</i>

682
00:58:36,931 --> 00:58:38,224
<i>or if he turns the tester down.</i>

683
00:58:38,307 --> 00:58:39,433
<i>That's not gonna work!</i>

684
00:58:39,516 --> 00:58:41,602
<i>I'm telling you. This works.</i>

685
00:58:41,685 --> 00:58:43,479
"Are you the loyalty tester?"

686
00:58:43,562 --> 00:58:46,690
<i>You're the only one</i>
<i>who's asked for a resume</i>

687
00:58:46,774 --> 00:58:49,568
<i>from a loyalty tester.</i>

688
00:58:49,652 --> 00:58:52,321
<i>Would you like to know</i>
<i>how many men I've tested?</i>

689
00:58:52,404 --> 00:58:55,282
<i>I don't treat this as a normal thing.</i>

690
00:58:55,366 --> 00:58:57,576
<i>I need assurance that this is safe.</i>

691
00:58:57,660 --> 00:58:59,495
<i>That I can trust you.</i>

692
00:59:00,913 --> 00:59:02,331
<i>How much is it again?</i>

693
00:59:02,414 --> 00:59:05,626
<i>It depends</i>
<i>on what you want me to do.</i>

694
00:59:05,709 --> 00:59:07,670
<i>You can decide whether...</i>

695
00:59:07,753 --> 00:59:09,588
<i>Fifty K, per week.</i>

696
00:59:10,172 --> 00:59:11,215
What?

697
00:59:11,298 --> 00:59:13,634
"What's the case, ma'am?"

698
00:59:13,717 --> 00:59:15,761
My husband is different.

699
00:59:15,844 --> 00:59:17,888
<i>Ben is keeping secrets from me.</i>

700
00:59:17,972 --> 00:59:19,723
<i>He's hiding something.</i>

701
00:59:19,807 --> 00:59:21,100
<i>All right, ma'am.</i>

702
00:59:21,183 --> 00:59:23,644
<i>Trailing, snooping,</i>

703
00:59:23,727 --> 00:59:25,396
<i>and spying on cheaters.</i>

704
00:59:25,479 --> 00:59:28,148
<i>That's our job.</i>

705
00:59:28,232 --> 00:59:31,443
Nanny! Get me some ice water!
I'm thirsty!

706
00:59:31,527 --> 00:59:34,238
<i>I want you to be honest with me.</i>

707
00:59:34,321 --> 00:59:37,741
<i>I can trust you, right?</i>

708
00:59:37,825 --> 00:59:39,159
<i>And I hope...</i>

709
00:59:39,243 --> 00:59:40,703
it's safe.

710
00:59:40,786 --> 00:59:42,454
I hope you're safe.

711
00:59:54,049 --> 00:59:56,593
<i> How does a woman</i>
<i>forgive a man who cheated on her?</i>

712
00:59:56,677 --> 00:59:58,178
I know he loves me!

713
00:59:58,262 --> 00:59:59,972
<i> After you gave him everything.</i>

714
01:00:00,055 --> 01:00:00,889
Fuck!

715
01:00:01,390 --> 01:00:02,683
<i> Your love...</i>

716
01:00:03,934 --> 01:00:05,311
<i>and your loyalty.</i>

717
01:00:07,479 --> 01:00:09,023
It will never happen to us.

718
01:00:10,566 --> 01:00:11,567
<i>Never.</i>

719
01:00:12,318 --> 01:00:13,360
<i>Hey...</i>

720
01:00:14,611 --> 01:00:17,990
<i>How long will you keep me hidden?</i>

721
01:00:18,073 --> 01:00:20,951
♪ <i>The longer that they stay hidden </i>♪

722
01:00:22,911 --> 01:00:25,497

